\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 his walk is cautious and insinuating; when he meets anyone in a narrow passage he is}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 always the first to stop and make way, and to say, not in a bass, as one would expect, but in}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 a high, soft tenor: "I beg your pardon!" He has a little swelling on his neck which prevents}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 him from wearing stiff starched collars, and so he always goes about in soft linen or cotton}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 shirts. Altogether he does not dress like a doctor. He wears the same suit for ten years, and}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 the new clothes, which he usually buys at a Jewish shop, look as shabby and crumpled on}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 him as his old ones; he sees patients and dines and pays visits all in the same coat; but this}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 is not due to niggardliness, but to complete carelessness about his appearance.}
